19
00:02:06,160 --> 00:02:07,067
[Luna Nest]

20
00:02:19,730 --> 00:02:22,980
Thank you, everyone!

21
00:02:22,980 --> 00:02:25,670
Thank you very much!

22
00:02:25,670 --> 00:02:27,930
- Minase!
- Yes?

23
00:02:27,930 --> 00:02:30,300
You messed up the choreography again.

24
00:02:30,300 --> 00:02:32,350
- Again?
- How many times is that now?

25
00:02:32,350 --> 00:02:33,810
I'm so sorry!

26
00:02:33,810 --> 00:02:36,780
You're all gonna stay to practice
for tomorrow.

27
00:02:36,780 --> 00:02:37,820
What?

28
00:02:37,820 --> 00:02:40,520
Come on, get to it.

29
00:02:40,520 --> 00:02:43,110
- I can't believe this.
- I'm sorry.

30
00:02:43,110 --> 00:02:46,366
- I'm sorry.
- Can't believe she screwed it up.

31
00:02:47,400 --> 00:02:50,980
Hey, aren't you thirsty?

32
00:02:51,810 --> 00:02:55,540
Yeah, 'cause a certain someone
made us stay late.

33
00:02:55,540 --> 00:02:58,210
Shall I go buy everyone drinks?

34
00:02:58,210 --> 00:03:01,600
Ama, that's so thoughtful of you!

35
00:03:01,600 --> 00:03:03,550
Thank you!

36
00:03:09,490 --> 00:03:12,220
Excuse me. We're filming right now.

37
00:03:12,220 --> 00:03:14,390
Would you mind waiting a bit?

38
00:03:14,390 --> 00:03:16,760
I'm so sorry.

39
00:03:16,760 --> 00:03:19,550
Excuse me, we have one person waiting.

40
00:03:19,550 --> 00:03:21,910
One person's waiting.

41
00:03:24,850 --> 00:03:27,330
I don't want to break up!

42
00:03:31,440 --> 00:03:34,680
Wow, a lovers' quarrel.

43
00:03:35,370 --> 00:03:37,450
I need to go.

44
00:03:37,450 --> 00:03:39,310
Wait, Chiaki! Please...

45
00:03:39,310 --> 00:03:41,080
Don't touch me!

46
00:03:49,171 --> 00:03:51,501
This is the worst...

47
00:04:12,660 --> 00:04:15,550
Sorry, I'll pay for it.

48
00:04:19,120 --> 00:04:23,440
Oh, but I don't have my wallet.

49
00:04:23,440 --> 00:04:27,190
My workplace is nearby.
Can you come with me?

50
00:04:27,190 --> 00:04:29,720
I-It's fine.

51
00:04:30,570 --> 00:04:35,630
After all, I can't just follow a stranger.

52
00:04:50,927 --> 00:04:53,760
You're Chiaki Hosho?

53
00:04:53,760 --> 00:04:56,640
Good, you know who I am.

54
00:04:56,640 --> 00:04:58,732
If you're going this way,

55
00:04:58,732 --> 00:05:02,443
could you be heading
to that rehearsal studio?

56
00:05:02,443 --> 00:05:04,430
Yes...

57
00:05:04,430 --> 00:05:08,370
Does that mean
we're in the same line of work?

58
00:05:08,370 --> 00:05:12,800
I'm just starting out,
but I'm technically an idol.

59
00:05:14,760 --> 00:05:18,740
Is that person from earlier
going to be okay?

60
00:05:20,230 --> 00:05:22,080
Oh...

61
00:05:24,100 --> 00:05:26,440
I'm in a bit of trouble.

62
00:05:26,440 --> 00:05:28,630
She's like a stalker.

63
00:05:28,630 --> 00:05:29,570
A stalker?

64
00:05:29,570 --> 00:05:33,360
But I guess it's kind of part of the job.

65
00:05:34,080 --> 00:05:36,300
That's rough.

66
00:05:38,220 --> 00:05:41,720
Actually, come with me.

67
00:05:48,080 --> 00:05:51,700
This time for real. Ready? Action!

68
00:05:55,680 --> 00:05:58,483
Thank you. Okay.

69
00:05:58,483 --> 00:06:00,027
- Prep for the next scene.
- Got it.

70
00:06:02,200 --> 00:06:03,570
Here.

71
00:06:04,490 --> 00:06:05,860
I don't need this much!

72
00:06:05,860 --> 00:06:08,490
But this is the only bill I have.

73
00:06:08,490 --> 00:06:12,740
It's 2,138 yen.
I can't accept more than that!

74
00:06:14,000 --> 00:06:16,730
You're interesting.

75
00:06:17,850 --> 00:06:21,610
I contacted the actress and her manager,
but I can't reach them!

76
00:06:21,610 --> 00:06:23,720
Huh, what do we do? Try calling.

77
00:06:23,720 --> 00:06:25,630
- Okay!
- Is something wrong?

78
00:06:25,630 --> 00:06:29,610
Mr. Hosho, it seems Ms. Hibiki took off.

79
00:06:29,610 --> 00:06:31,650
Is that so...

80
00:06:31,650 --> 00:06:33,300
Took off?

81
00:06:36,990 --> 00:06:39,169
[Anna Saotome]

82
00:06:40,540 --> 00:06:42,150
<i>What's taking so long?</i>

83
00:06:42,150 --> 00:06:43,980
Everyone's worried about you.

84
00:06:43,980 --> 00:06:45,150
<i>I'm so sorry.</i>

85
00:06:45,150 --> 00:06:47,790
I actually spilled the drinks on my way back,

86
00:06:47,790 --> 00:06:50,941
and I have to go buy them again.

87
00:06:54,080 --> 00:06:57,660
My apologies, my name is Chiaki Hosho.

88
00:06:57,660 --> 00:07:00,090
Could I please speak with her manager?

89
00:07:00,090 --> 00:07:01,960
Huh, seriously? Chiaki Hosho?

90
00:07:01,960 --> 00:07:03,690
- Seriously?
- Huh?

91
00:07:03,690 --> 00:07:05,970
Hey, Mr. Suzui!

92
00:07:05,970 --> 00:07:08,040
It's... It's Chiaki Hosho.

93
00:07:08,040 --> 00:07:09,450
Yes?

94
00:07:09,450 --> 00:07:14,210
Would it be okay
if I borrowed Ms. Minase for a bit?

95
00:07:14,210 --> 00:07:19,880
I'd like to ask her to be the replacement
for an actress who bailed.

96
00:07:19,880 --> 00:07:21,250
Huh?

97
00:07:30,440 --> 00:07:32,240
<i>What do I do?</i>

98
00:07:32,240 --> 00:07:35,890
<i>Even if it's just this one line.</i>

99
00:07:35,890 --> 00:07:39,035
[I love you. I've always loved you.]

100
00:07:40,270 --> 00:07:43,790
Sorry for asking so suddenly.

101
00:07:44,760 --> 00:07:48,260
Well, I don't think I can do it after all.

102
00:07:48,260 --> 00:07:51,240
I've never done any acting before.

103
00:07:51,240 --> 00:07:54,290
You're an idol, right?

104
00:07:54,990 --> 00:07:56,990
Yes.

105
00:07:56,990 --> 00:08:00,990
It could be a chance
to expand your work, you know?

106
00:08:02,670 --> 00:08:03,992
<i>That's true.</i>

107
00:08:03,992 --> 00:08:06,080
<i>As a not-so-successful idol like me,</i>

108
00:08:06,080 --> 00:08:10,680
<i>I rarely get the chance to be on a drama set.</i>

109
00:08:12,650 --> 00:08:17,020
<i>Alright! This is my one and only big stage!</i>

110
00:08:21,530 --> 00:08:26,030
Here you go. We're about to start.

111
00:08:31,610 --> 00:08:34,170
Don't be so nervous.

112
00:08:34,170 --> 00:08:36,530
We can redo it, so it's okay.

113
00:08:37,470 --> 00:08:39,360
Okay!

114
00:08:39,360 --> 00:08:41,480
Alright, we're starting!

115
00:08:42,110 --> 00:08:44,880
Take one. Ready? Action!

116
00:08:54,900 --> 00:08:57,310
Just leave me alone.

117
00:09:01,280 --> 00:09:03,880
<i>I can't let the pressure get to me.</i>

118
00:09:05,600 --> 00:09:07,260
<i>My character is a girl</i>

119
00:09:07,260 --> 00:09:11,720
<i>who harbors feelings
for the young man played by Mr. Hosho.</i>

120
00:09:11,720 --> 00:09:14,010
<i>It's a quick scene,</i>

121
00:09:14,010 --> 00:09:18,480
<i>but to her, it's an important one
where she gets over a crush she's had.</i>

122
00:09:20,810 --> 00:09:22,219
<i>That's right.</i>

123
00:09:22,219 --> 00:09:25,080
<i>If I think back to that moment...</i>

124
00:09:29,370 --> 00:09:30,910
<i>Ama.</i>

125
00:09:34,670 --> 00:09:36,250
I love you.

126
00:09:40,180 --> 00:09:44,160
I've always loved you.

127
00:09:55,840 --> 00:09:58,160
Cut! Okay!

128
00:09:58,160 --> 00:09:59,830
Cut! Okay!

129
00:10:02,190 --> 00:10:06,690
<i>Good, I didn't cause any trouble.</i>

130
00:10:08,860 --> 00:10:11,290
Hello, I'm Suzui, her manager.

131
00:10:11,290 --> 00:10:15,220
Thank you for working with Minase today.

132
00:10:15,220 --> 00:10:17,120
Thank you.

133
00:10:17,120 --> 00:10:20,560
We'll get going now,
so you can focus on the shoot.

134
00:10:33,750 --> 00:10:36,120
I'm home!

135
00:10:36,120 --> 00:10:37,850
Welcome back, Sis!

136
00:10:37,850 --> 00:10:39,010
Welcome home!

137
00:10:39,010 --> 00:10:40,170
What were you doing?

138
00:10:40,170 --> 00:10:42,870
Today, I was out shopping.

139
00:10:42,870 --> 00:10:43,960
Welcome home.

140
00:10:43,960 --> 00:10:45,180
Mom, go back to sleep.

141
00:10:45,180 --> 00:10:47,170
You had a fever again this morning.

142
00:10:47,170 --> 00:10:48,570
Sorry again.

143
00:10:48,570 --> 00:10:51,380
It's okay. I'll get dinner ready now.

144
00:10:51,380 --> 00:10:52,410
Thanks.

145
00:10:52,410 --> 00:10:54,520
I'll help make dinner too.
[50% off]

146
00:10:54,520 --> 00:10:57,125
- Me too!
- Really?

147
00:10:57,125 --> 00:10:59,133
What are you making?

148
00:10:59,133 --> 00:11:01,380
- A bookmark.
- I see.

149
00:11:01,850 --> 00:11:06,290
<i>It was only one line, but it was fun.</i>

150
00:11:07,820 --> 00:11:12,480
<i>I hope I get to do acting work again someday.</i>

151
00:11:14,530 --> 00:11:17,840
What? A movie starring Hosho?

152
00:11:17,840 --> 00:11:20,950
It's the production team from that drama.

153
00:11:21,760 --> 00:11:24,440
A youth drama set in a music college.

154
00:11:24,440 --> 00:11:26,390
You'll be a student.

155
00:11:26,390 --> 00:11:30,744
Apparently, Mr. Hosho recommended you
after seeing your acting.

156
00:11:30,744 --> 00:11:35,850
It's a dream come true,
but why would Mr. Hosho...

157
00:11:35,850 --> 00:11:38,430
By the way, the pay is...

158
00:11:40,650 --> 00:11:43,080
<i>A month's worth of groceries?</i>

159
00:11:43,850 --> 00:11:47,206
I'll do it! Please let me do it!

160
00:11:47,206 --> 00:11:48,475
Alright.

161
00:11:48,475 --> 00:11:51,620
[Our Ensemble]

162
00:11:52,780 --> 00:11:54,380
Minase.

163
00:11:54,380 --> 00:11:56,210
- Yes?
- Listen, okay?

164
00:11:56,210 --> 00:11:58,320
No matter how close you get to him,

165
00:11:58,320 --> 00:12:01,730
don't make any mistakes with Mr. Hosho,
alright?

166
00:12:02,400 --> 00:12:04,340
A mistake?

167
00:12:04,340 --> 00:12:07,650
He's from a major agency. We're a tiny one.

168
00:12:07,650 --> 00:12:11,820
If something happens,
you'd be the one to suffer for it.

169
00:12:11,820 --> 00:12:13,660
Oh, there's no way.

170
00:12:13,660 --> 00:12:15,060
That'd never happen.

171
00:12:15,060 --> 00:12:19,010
How could I ever, with a star like that?

172
00:12:19,010 --> 00:12:20,730
Yeah, I suppose not.

173
00:12:26,970 --> 00:12:28,480
[Our Ensemble]
[Ama Minase]

174
00:12:38,500 --> 00:12:40,940
Here's Ama Minase, playing Kanon.

175
00:12:40,940 --> 00:12:41,890
Thank you.

176
00:12:41,890 --> 00:12:45,680
- We're counting on you.
- Thank you.

177
00:12:47,480 --> 00:12:49,260
You're amazing.

178
00:12:49,260 --> 00:12:52,850
That... That's not true.

179
00:12:52,850 --> 00:12:55,440
Cut! Cut! You blinked!

180
00:12:55,440 --> 00:12:58,460
Sorry, sorry.

181
00:12:58,460 --> 00:13:02,100
I really love when you play, Tatsumi.

182
00:13:02,100 --> 00:13:05,070
- Cut!
- Cut! You flipped your line!

183
00:13:05,070 --> 00:13:06,556
- One more time.
- I'm so sorry!

184
00:13:06,556 --> 00:13:07,960
- It's okay.
- So sorry.

185
00:13:07,960 --> 00:13:10,390
Ready? Action!

186
00:13:12,530 --> 00:13:14,590
I'm not at my best lately.

187
00:13:14,590 --> 00:13:16,300
What's wrong?

188
00:13:18,136 --> 00:13:19,806
My fingers...

189
00:13:20,480 --> 00:13:22,990
They can't keep up with my feelings.

190
00:13:23,720 --> 00:13:26,410
Don't be so whiny.

191
00:13:26,410 --> 00:13:28,029
You don't have to put it like that.

192
00:13:28,029 --> 00:13:32,670
You guys wouldn't understand how I feel.

193
00:13:32,670 --> 00:13:34,360
Wait!

194
00:13:35,860 --> 00:13:37,550
- Cut!
- Cut!

195
00:13:37,550 --> 00:13:39,330
- Hey!
- Are you okay?

196
00:13:39,330 --> 00:13:41,970
- I'm sorry.
- Why did you fall? Get the first aid kit.

197
00:13:41,970 --> 00:13:44,530
- Can you get up?
- I'm sorry.

198
00:13:45,650 --> 00:13:47,109
[Our Ensemble]
[Ama Minase]

199
00:13:52,560 --> 00:13:54,850
Good work on the first day.

200
00:13:57,930 --> 00:14:00,030
Good work today.

201
00:14:00,780 --> 00:14:05,110
Sorry for causing so much trouble.

202
00:14:05,920 --> 00:14:08,850
I was like that at first too.

203
00:14:08,850 --> 00:14:11,540
Even for a minor role,
I'd do take after take.

204
00:14:11,540 --> 00:14:16,500
The set felt tense,
and we'd run over schedule.

205
00:14:17,510 --> 00:14:22,350
You went through that too, Mr. Hosho?

206
00:14:22,350 --> 00:14:24,370
Of course I did.

207
00:14:27,200 --> 00:14:33,150
You know, I think you have
talent for acting, Ms. Minase.

208
00:14:33,760 --> 00:14:35,250
Huh?

209
00:14:35,250 --> 00:14:37,200
I mean it.

210
00:14:37,200 --> 00:14:41,710
I could tell just from acting
in that one scene with you.

211
00:14:41,710 --> 00:14:46,510
You were so immersed in your character,
I couldn't tell it was your first time.

212
00:14:47,340 --> 00:14:49,980
Hearing that from you...

213
00:14:49,980 --> 00:14:53,690
I'll take them to heart
and give it my all until the very end!

214
00:14:54,630 --> 00:14:56,790
So dramatic.

215
00:14:58,830 --> 00:15:00,370
Oh, right.

216
00:15:00,370 --> 00:15:04,410
Can I call you by your first name?

217
00:15:05,690 --> 00:15:08,040
There's also a staff member named Ms. Minase,

218
00:15:08,040 --> 00:15:10,690
so it might get confusing.

219
00:15:10,690 --> 00:15:13,910
Oh, I see.

220
00:15:13,910 --> 00:15:16,553
- My name is...
- Ama.

221
00:15:17,270 --> 00:15:19,550
It's a cute name.

222
00:15:22,640 --> 00:15:27,910
You can call me "Chiaki", if you want.

223
00:15:29,100 --> 00:15:30,350
Huh?

224
00:15:31,120 --> 00:15:32,850
Try it.

225
00:15:35,550 --> 00:15:37,920
Chiaki?

226
00:15:39,280 --> 00:15:40,640
Yeah.

227
00:15:46,250 --> 00:15:50,340
Oh, right, about your next scene...

228
00:15:54,000 --> 00:15:56,890
<i>Listen, okay?
No matter how close you get to him,</i>

229
00:15:56,890 --> 00:16:00,300
<i>don't make any mistakes
with Mr. Hosho, alright?</i>

230
00:16:04,490 --> 00:16:08,750
Oh, no, you see...

231
00:16:10,140 --> 00:16:11,850
Chiaki.

232
00:16:19,730 --> 00:16:24,030
This is Shiki Motomiya,
a member of my old idol group.

233
00:16:24,030 --> 00:16:27,100
He has a cameo in this movie.

234
00:16:27,100 --> 00:16:28,430
Hello.

235
00:16:28,430 --> 00:16:31,630
Nice to meet you, I'm Ama Minase.

236
00:16:34,820 --> 00:16:38,430
Oh, I should get going soon.

237
00:16:38,430 --> 00:16:40,270
Yeah, see you.

238
00:16:40,270 --> 00:16:41,880
See you.

239
00:16:48,770 --> 00:16:52,040
Is that girl your new interest, Chiaki?

240
00:16:52,040 --> 00:16:53,470
Yeah.

241
00:16:53,470 --> 00:16:56,480
Getting bothered by that weird woman
was worth it.

242
00:16:56,480 --> 00:16:59,910
Can't you stop doing that already?

243
00:16:59,910 --> 00:17:02,760
You're a good guy, Shiki, unlike me.

244
00:17:02,760 --> 00:17:05,410
That's not what I meant.

245
00:17:07,480 --> 00:17:10,280
When you finally find
someone you actually love,

246
00:17:10,280 --> 00:17:12,470
it'll only cause you trouble.

247
00:17:13,450 --> 00:17:15,270
It's fine.

248
00:17:16,380 --> 00:17:20,740
I'll never get serious about anyone
until the day I die.

249
00:17:26,716 --> 00:17:28,486
Thanks for today.

250
00:17:31,081 --> 00:17:33,231
Here, this is for the taxi.

251
00:17:38,575 --> 00:17:41,770
Thank you very much!

252
00:17:43,942 --> 00:17:45,430
And...

253
00:17:45,430 --> 00:17:48,755
Oh, I'll make sure you get some work too.

254
00:17:48,755 --> 00:17:51,245
I'll hold you to it.

255
00:17:57,852 --> 00:18:00,002
Die.

256
00:18:01,410 --> 00:18:06,930
Die! You're so disgusting, you fat ass!

257
00:18:06,930 --> 00:18:12,430
If you weren't a producer,
I wouldn't even bother with you!

258
00:18:15,890 --> 00:18:17,470
[Chiaki Hosho Cast in Lead Role!]
[Latest On-Set Photos for "Our Ensemble"]

259
00:18:17,470 --> 00:18:19,350
[Congratulations on the start of filming!]

260
00:18:21,084 --> 00:18:25,310
Why does that third-rate idol,
who can't even sing or dance,

261
00:18:25,310 --> 00:18:28,480
get to be in Chiaki Hosho's movie?

262
00:18:31,760 --> 00:18:34,510
God, she's such an eyesore.

263
00:18:35,340 --> 00:18:38,560
I wish she'd just disappear from my sight.

264
00:18:43,260 --> 00:18:48,420
I just got a great idea!

265
00:18:51,030 --> 00:18:53,399
[Minase]

266
00:18:53,399 --> 00:18:56,308
I look forward to...

267
00:18:57,159 --> 00:18:58,663
I look forward to...

268
00:18:59,110 --> 00:19:01,067
Sis, act for us!

269
00:19:01,067 --> 00:19:02,444
- What?
- I wanna see!

270
00:19:02,444 --> 00:19:03,484
- You wanna see?
- Yup.

271
00:19:03,484 --> 00:19:06,370
Okay, which line should I do?

272
00:19:06,370 --> 00:19:09,380
I don't have many lines.

273
00:19:09,380 --> 00:19:10,920
How about this one?

274
00:19:10,920 --> 00:19:12,410
This one? The heroine's line, huh?

275
00:19:12,410 --> 00:19:15,030
The heroine's line, huh?

276
00:19:16,630 --> 00:19:18,240
Alright.

277
00:19:21,140 --> 00:19:25,910
My heart still echoes with your song,

278
00:19:26,680 --> 00:19:29,380
with feelings of love.

279
00:19:30,340 --> 00:19:31,822
- That was great!
- Really?

280
00:19:31,822 --> 00:19:33,780
Maybe I'll do one more scene then.

281
00:19:33,780 --> 00:19:35,520
Yay!

282
00:19:48,040 --> 00:19:50,690
My drama is number one in ratings
this season.

283
00:19:50,690 --> 00:19:52,850
By a landslide.

284
00:19:52,850 --> 00:19:54,160
Yeah, so I hear.

285
00:19:54,160 --> 00:19:59,070
That producer who looked down on me
when I was starting out

286
00:19:59,070 --> 00:20:02,230
got ranked "most disappointing".

287
00:20:02,230 --> 00:20:04,960
It feels so damn good.

288
00:20:07,500 --> 00:20:10,780
You seem pretty happy too, Chiaki.

289
00:20:10,780 --> 00:20:14,670
Did you find your true love?

290
00:20:14,670 --> 00:20:16,220
No way.

291
00:20:17,090 --> 00:20:21,340
The girl I'm working on
is harder to reel in than usual.

292
00:20:23,150 --> 00:20:26,240
Huh, that's rare.

293
00:20:26,240 --> 00:20:29,742
It's usually so easy, I get bored.

294
00:20:29,742 --> 00:20:31,570
This is actually more fun.

295
00:20:33,860 --> 00:20:38,240
So? What's she like? Cute?

296
00:20:39,703 --> 00:20:43,063
Her face is cute, I guess.

297
00:20:43,780 --> 00:20:46,370
She's plain and kind of serious.

298
00:20:49,521 --> 00:20:53,850
Let's play a harmony, you and I.

299
00:20:53,850 --> 00:20:56,790
Wow, amazing! So good!

300
00:20:56,790 --> 00:20:58,530
<i>But...</i>

301
00:20:59,280 --> 00:21:03,410
I love seeing how girls
from a happy household would look

302
00:21:03,410 --> 00:21:08,730
when they make that look of despair.

303
00:21:12,020 --> 00:21:16,230
Oh, man. You're the absolute worst.

304
00:21:16,230 --> 00:21:19,450
But that's classic Chiaki.

305
00:21:20,440 --> 00:21:23,480
Shiki told me to stop, though.

306
00:21:23,480 --> 00:21:27,460
Well, he's a goody-two-shoes.

307
00:21:28,240 --> 00:21:32,160
Oh, hey, let's make a bet.

308
00:21:32,160 --> 00:21:35,050
Whether you can get that girl or not.

309
00:21:36,572 --> 00:21:40,272
If you can't get her in three months,

310
00:21:42,480 --> 00:21:44,650
give me that watch.

311
00:21:46,740 --> 00:21:49,630
Well... sure.

312
00:21:49,630 --> 00:21:52,290
Oh? What's this?

313
00:21:52,290 --> 00:21:53,570
Not confident?

314
00:21:53,570 --> 00:21:55,440
Don't be stupid.

315
00:21:56,030 --> 00:21:57,490
That's the spirit.

316
00:21:57,490 --> 00:22:01,640
Oh, Chiaki, Kai! You came!

317
00:22:01,640 --> 00:22:02,690
We sure did.

318
00:22:02,690 --> 00:22:03,870
Let's sit!

319
00:22:03,870 --> 00:22:06,460
- What are you feeling?
- How about tequila?

320
00:22:06,460 --> 00:22:08,050
Tequila to start? Both of you?

321
00:22:08,050 --> 00:22:09,480
- Tequila.
- Both of us.

322
00:22:09,480 --> 00:22:11,790
Tequila? Well, if we have to!

323
00:22:11,790 --> 00:22:13,224
Hey, that's fast...

324
00:23:35,249 --> 00:23:37,000
You should rely on me more.

325
00:23:37,000 --> 00:23:39,420
What am I thinking?

326
00:23:39,420 --> 00:23:40,670
The necklace is gone.

327
00:23:40,670 --> 00:23:42,517
Are you accusing me of stealing it?

328
00:23:42,517 --> 00:23:44,650
How about me? We're playing lovers.

329
00:23:44,650 --> 00:23:46,870
No. Ama is mine.

330
00:23:46,870 --> 00:23:50,100
If you'd like,
why don't you stay for dinner?

